project: The tablets that hold all the Jewish values have been lost in the desert and they're at risk of being mixed up with the ones for Christian values. It's up to you to preserve the history of Judaism by gathering all of the tablet pieces. Use the arrow keys to wander the desert and collect the tablet pieces, avoiding the Christian missionaries as you go. On each tablet, click on which value is not a Jewish value to earn Mitzvah points and elevate the world.

This game handles many complicated ethical questions from the Jewish lens. As with everything in Judaism, the answer is often "it's complicated." I am not a Rabbi and am not qualified to give you Jewish advice on your specific problems. If you have a question, consult your local Rabbi.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) Our sense of right and wrong comes from the Bible

In Judaism, morals and ethics come from as variety of sources, not just the Tanakh (the Jewish Bible). Halacha, Jewish laws written by historic rabbis and inspired by the written and Oral Torah, are the governing rules of right and wrong, but there are also separate Jewish customs and an emphasis on following the moral code of the people one is living with.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) Same-sex marriage goes against the Scripture
B) Human life is of infinite value

Homosexuality is a complicated subject in Judaism and different denominations have different feelings about what is right or wrong. Many Orthodox Jews believe that homosexual relationships are not advised by G-d, but many Conservative and Reform Jews believe in a different reading of the laws in Leviticus and have no problem with it.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?

Like most ethical questions in Judaism, the question of abortion is complicated. Judaism has a concept called pikuach nefesh, translated as "watching over a soul", that teaches that the preservation of human life overrides virtually any other religious rule. So in the case of a fetus causing the mother harm to her physical or mental health, many rabbis believe abortion is not only okay but necessary. These decisions are made on a case by case basis with the person and their individual Rabbi.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) Males should lead in a marriage
B) You should have no other gods

Jewish mysticism, called Kabbalah, talks about the differences between men and women on a spiritual level and how those affect which actions they are best suited for; however, marriage in Judaism is meant to be an equal relationship between both man and woman. Gender roles in Judaism vary based on denomination, but all denominations prize an equal and loving relationship between spouses regardless of gender.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
B) Only men may be faith leaders
A) Respect of parents is of utmost importance

Women are allowed to become Rabbis in Reform and Conservative congregations, and it has been growing in popularity even in the Orthodox world. Rabbis are a bit different from Christian faith leaders as the emphasis for a Rabbi is not on leading services but on being a teacher for anyone who wishes to learn.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
B) Adam and Eve brought about sin
A) People should give to charity

The Christian concept of original sin does not exist in Judaism. In the Adam and Eve (named Chava in Hebrew) story in the Torah, eating the fruit of the tree does not bring about sin, but instead makes Adam and Chava mortal to allow them to reach the Earth to complete their purpose of starting human kind. Sin is a concept in Judaism but it is not given much weight; Jews are asked to complete Mitzvot, aka commandments, not because of a fear of eternal damnation, but because it is the right thing to do.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) Capital punishment is ok for the crime of murder
B) The commandment against murder does not prohibit war

The majority of rabbis agree that capital punishment is never acceptable under Jewish law as it transgresses the commandment not to murder. Jewish law in the time of the Temple did have written capital punishment in the law, but these punishments were only there as a warning and never actually carried out.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
B) We should not fear death

In Judaism, suicide only transgresses the prohibition against murder if the person is in completely sound mind when they take their life, which is rarely ever true. People who commit suicide due to mental disorders, addictions, etc. are considered to be killed by the disease not by themselves.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
B) Alcohol should be avoided or used very moderately
A) Marriage is a covenant before God

While Judaism does have prohibitions against extremely excessive drinking that may lead to crime or hurting others, alcohol is a major part of Jewish ritual. A prayer is said over wine every Friday evening and there are two holidays where it is actually a commandment for anyone over the legal drinking age who can drink to get drunk in order to celebrate the happiness of the day.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) After life, there is either heaven or hell
B) Racial discrimination should not be tolerated

The idea of the Jewish afterlife varies depending on who you ask (in general, Jews spend much more time thinking about how to improve this life than worrying about what happens after death). There is no concept of hell and the most popular afterlife belief is that souls who have completed enough Mitzvot enter the garden of eden while those who have not return to earth in a different body to complete more.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) Women are commanded to have children
B) Adultery is a serious sin

While it is a commandment in Judaism for a man to get married and have children, that commandment is not levied on women. This is because having a child could have historically been likely to lead to the death of the woman in childbirth, and preserving human life is more important than nearly any commandment.
Which of these "Judeo-Christian" values is not actually a Jewish value?
A) God created only two genders

In the Torah there are actually six genders referenced: men who have male genitalia, women who have male genitalia, men who have female genitalia, women who have male genitalia, people who have both sets of genitalia, and people who have none. In the story of Adam and Eve, Adam is born androgynous, with both sets of genitalia.
